<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-248-452  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 248 452.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Lasers andamp; Optronics  March 1990 v9 n3 p20(2).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Optical amplifiers star at OFC. (Optical Fiber CommunicationConference)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Hecht, Jeff.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Several important experiments are reported at the 1990 OpticalFiber Communication Conference concerning erbium-doped fiberamplifiers.andP;  Experiments from different research centers showerbium amplifiers to be well-suited to extending transmissiondistances and raising signal power.andP;  These results show promisefor erbium amplifiers replacing electronic repeaters inapplications like submarine cables where repeaters must bereplaced often.andP;  Demonstrations also show that erbium amplifierscan handle coherent communications, wavelength-divisionmultiplexed signals and soliton pulses.andP;  The most impressiveresults at the conference show transmission of 2.488 gigabits persecond through 2223 kilometers of dispersion-shifted fiber.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Topic:     Optical Fiber Communication ConferenceFiber OpticsAmplifiersEnhancementsOptoelectronic DevicesData Communications.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>